how can i get white clothes that have now turned pink back to bright white again i made the mistake not the first time either of washing a red garment or two with my whites i generally don't separate the colors so now a lot of my whities are pink so how can i get them back to white again i assume you washed your whites with something red in the load that's a toughie rit dye makes a product called color remover that can help it's available in the grocery store usually in the aisle that has the laundry detergent or perhaps near the cleaning stuff if that doesn't do it try a chlorine bleach soak fill the tub of the washer add a couple of cups of bleach and add the clothes agitate a few minutes and then let soak check frequently and finish the load as soon as possible bleach will literally eat fabrics given time Textile manufacturing Washing machine Laundry detergent Dry cleaning Upholstery Dishwashing Hydrogen peroxide Technicolor Sodium hypochlorite Laundry Dairy Bleach Weaving Tofu Diaper Menstrual cup Detergent Water purification Hair coloring Leather Brewery Wood pulp Sodium percarbonate Mattress Western blot Sewage treatment Bleeding Light-emitting diode Kimono Clothing Casting Knitting Tattoo Staining (biology) Textile The Amazing Race White bread Chlorine Vinegar Tanning Japanese tea ceremony Molotov cocktail Textile manufacturing terminology Motor oil Menstrual cycle Common bean Laundromat Undergarment Handloading Hemp Sodium perborate CPU cache Supermarket Urticaria Champagne (beverage) Haloalkane Coir Lionel Corporation C-41 process Hummingbird Han Chinese clothing Trisodium phosphate Jute Mouth ulcer Clothing terminology Hygiene Cruising (maritime) Fecal incontinence Wok Cochineal Indigo dye Sake Swimming pool Hat Kilt Color Endowment (Mormonism) Coffee Sodium hydroxide Phosphorus Bulk vending Sterilization (microbiology) Pottery Linen System/34 Time Out of Mind Ironing Fischer Random Chess Cashmere wool Procter & Gamble Skinhead Flour Hamster Industrial was